Viterbo) which is discussed and well reproduced in Franzsepp Würtenberger, Mannerism, London [New York: Holt, Rinehart & Winston], 1963 (original German edition, Schroll, Vienna 1962), p. 151f, colour pl. p. 153. According to Würtenberger commissioned by Vicino Orsini, c. 1560, the park within sight of Orsini castle; André CHASTEL, The Crisis of the Renaissance, [1520-1600, Geneva] (Skira), English language edition 1968, p. 140 has reproduction of Dragon fighting a lion and a lioness 1552, sculpture in Tufa rock. column4: <content>BRUEGEL: Dulle Griet (1562) The head of Hell comparable to the head of Monster, one of, the garden sculptures in the garden of Bomarzo (nr. Viterbo) which is discussed and well reproduced in Franzsepp Würtenberger, Mannerism, London [New York: Holt, Rinehart & Winston], 1963 (original German edition, Schroll, Vienna 1962), p. 151f, colour pl. p. 153. According to Würtenberger commissioned by Vicino Orsini, c. 1560, the park within sight of Orsini castle; André CHASTEL, The Crisis of the Renaissance, [1520-1600, Geneva] (Skira), English language edition 1968, p. 140 has reproduction of Dragon fighting a lion and a lioness 1552, sculpture in Tufa rock. Castle Park Bomarzo near Viterbo; [verso][toegevoegde vermeldling]: 'F.G. neither Würtenberger nor Chastel give the designer's or sculptor's name.</content>

<part_of.title>Korte inhoud: [Taal, Frans] Herkomst 'Dulle Griet': Collectie Hammer, Stockholm (verkoopscatalogus, Heberle, 05-10-1894, n° 48), eerdere verzameling Brogren. Vraagt, op last van Burchard, advies over herkomst. [toegevoegde vermelding]: 'Look up Lugt II [= Frits Lugt, Répertoire des catalogues de ventes publiques intéressant l'art ou la curiosité : tableaux, dessins, estampes, miniatures, sculptures, bronzes, émaux, vitraux, tapisseries, céramiques, objets d'art, meubles, antiquités, monnaies, médailles, camées, intailles, armes, instruments, curiosités naturelles, etc. II : deuxième période : 1826-1860, La Haye: Nijhoff, 1953; Mireur [= Hippolyte Mireur, Dictionnaire des ventes d'art faites en France et à l'étranger pendant les XVIIIme & XIXme siècles : tableaux, dessins, estampes, aquarelles, miniatures, pastels, gouaches, sépias, fusains, emaux, eventails peints & vitraux,7 vols., Paris: Maison d'éditions d'oeuvres artistiques, 1911-1912].</part_of.title>
